TITLE: Mutation with @appendNode
DESCRIPTION: This example shows a Relay mutation using the `@appendNode` directive to add a new node to a connection.  The mutation takes a `$connections` variable and uses `@appendNode` on the `feedbackCommentNode` field, specifying the `edgeTypeName` as "CommentsEdge". This directive automatically creates an edge wrapping the new node and appends it to the specified connections.
