TITLE: Demonstrating Relay's Normalized Data Representation from GraphQL Response
DESCRIPTION: This example illustrates how Relay normalizes a GraphQL response into its internal record-based representation. It shows the transformation from a GraphQL fragment and response object into a normalized RecordSource with separate records for each entity, linked by references.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/relay/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-v18.0.0/principles-and-architecture/runtime-architecture.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// GraphQL Fragment
fragment on User {
  id
  name
  address {
    city
  }
}

// Response
{
  id: '842472',
  name: 'Joe',
  address: {
    city: 'Seattle',
  }
}

// Normalized Representation
RecordSource {
  '842472': Record {
    __id: '842472',
    __typename: 'User', // the type is known statically from the fragment
    id: '842472',
    name: 'Joe',
    address: {__ref: 'client:842472:address'}, // link to another record
  },
  'client:842472:address': Record {
    // A client ID, derived from the path from parent & parent's ID
    __id: 'client:842472:address',
    __typename: 'Address',
    city: 'Seattle',
  }
}
```

