LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const React = require('React');

type State = {error: ?Error};

class ErrorBoundary extends React.Component<Props, State> {
  static getDerivedStateFromError(error): State {
    // Set some state derived from the caught error
    return {error: error};
  }
}
```

