TITLE: Demonstrating FlattenTransform in GraphQL
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how the FlattenTransform reduces extraneous levels of indirection in a GraphQL query by inlining fields from anonymous fragments that match the parent type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/relay/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-v17.0.0/principles-and-architecture/compiler-architecture.md#2025-04-18_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: graphql
CODE:
```
# before: `id` is processed twice
foo { # type FooType
   id
   ... on FooType { # matches the parent type, so this is extraneous
     id
   }
 }

 # after: `id` is processed once
 foo {
   id
 }
```

