TITLE: Reading Fragment Data with Relay Resolvers in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to use `readFragment()` within a Relay Resolver to access data from a specified GraphQL fragment. The function takes a fragment key as input, reads the necessary data using `readFragment()`, and returns a derived value (in this case, a full name) based on the fragment data. This resolver ensures recomputation when data in the fragment changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/relay/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-v17.0.0/api-reference/relay-resolvers/runtime-functions.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import {readFragment} from "relay-runtime";

/**
 * @RelayResolver User.fullName: String
 * @rootFragment UserFullNameFragment
 */
export function fullName(key: UserFullNameFragment$key): string {
  const user = readFragment(graphql`
    fragment UserFullNameFragment on User {
      firstName
      lastName
    }
  `, key);
  return `${user.firstName} ${user.lastName}`;
}
```

