TITLE: GraphQL Fetch Helper Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Utility function to handle GraphQL requests to GitHub's API with proper authentication and request formatting.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/relay/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-experimental/RelayHooks-StepByStep.md#2025-04-18_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async function fetchGraphQL(text, variables) {
  const REACT_APP_GITHUB_AUTH_TOKEN = process.env.REACT_APP_GITHUB_AUTH_TOKEN;

  // Fetch data from GitHub's GraphQL API:
  const response = await fetch('https://api.github.com/graphql', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      Authorization: `bearer ${REACT_APP_GITHUB_AUTH_TOKEN}`,
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      query: text,
      variables,
    }),
  });

  // Get the response as JSON
  return await response.json();
}

export default fetchGraphQL;
```

