TITLE: Using @alias with @required
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use `@alias` with `@required(action: NONE)` to group required fields. If any of the fields inside the aliased fragment are null, the entire aliased field will be null, allowing for a single null check.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/relay/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-v17.0.0/guides/alias-directive.md#2025-04-18_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function MyUser({userKey}) {
  const user = useFragment(graphql`
    fragment MyFragment on User {
      id
      ... @alias(as: \"requiredFields\") {
        name @required(action: NONE)
        email @required(action: NONE)
      }
    }`, userKey);

  if(user.requiredFields == null) {
    return `Missing required fields for user ${user.id}`;
  }
  return `Hello ${user.requiredFields.name} (${user.requiredFields.email}).!`;
}
```

