TITLE: Using @alias for type safety
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates the use of the `@alias` directive to improve type safety when spreading a fragment. By aliasing the `MyViewer` fragment, the component can safely check if the underlying data satisfies the type requirements of `MyViewer` before passing it to the component.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/relay/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-v17.0.0/guides/alias-directive.md#2025-04-18_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function MyNode({nodeKey}) {
  const node = useFragment(graphql`
    fragment MyFragment on Node {
      ...MyViewer @alias(as: \"my_viewer\")
    }`, nodeKey);

  // Relay returns the fragment key as its own nullable property
  if(node.my_viewer == null) {
    return null;
  }

  // Because `my_viewer` is typed as nullable, Flow/TypeScript will
  // show an error if you try to use the `my_viewer` without first
  // performing a null check.
  //                          VVVVVVVVVVVVVV
  return <MyViewer viewerKey={node.my_viewer} />
}
```

