TITLE: Reading Fragment Data in Relay Resolver (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use readFragment() function in a Relay Resolver to derive a User's full name from firstName and lastName fields. This function is specifically for use in Relay Resolvers and will throw an error if used elsewhere.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/relay/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-v18.0.0/api-reference/relay-resolvers/runtime-functions.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import {readFragment} from "relay-runtime";

/**
 * @RelayResolver User.fullName: String
 * @rootFragment UserFullNameFragment
 */
export function fullName(key: UserFullNameFragment$key): string {
  const user = readFragment(graphql`
    fragment UserFullNameFragment on User {
      firstName
      lastName
    }
  `, key);
  return `${user.firstName} ${user.lastName}`;
}
```

