TITLE: Configuring Network Layer with graphql-ws for GraphQL Subscriptions in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to configure the Network Layer using the graphql-ws library to handle GraphQL subscriptions over WebSockets. It creates a WebSocket client and defines a subscribe function that creates an Observable for each subscription operation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/relay/blob/main/website/versioned_docs/version-v17.0.0/guided-tour/updating-data/graphql-subscriptions.md#2025-04-18_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {
    ...
    Network,
    Observable
} from 'relay-runtime';
import { createClient } from 'graphql-ws';

const wsClient = createClient({
  url:'ws://localhost:3000',
});

const subscribe = (operation, variables) => {
  return Observable.create((sink) => {
    return wsClient.subscribe(
      {
        operationName: operation.name,
        query: operation.text,
        variables,
      },
      sink,
    );
  });
}

const network = Network.create(fetchQuery, subscribe);
```

